latestIgtvVideos.title: The Influencer Scam| Dreams vs Reality
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Being an influencer takes Years of consistent Hardwork & passion.
The popular faces you see now @prernachhabra @komalpandeyofficial @i_am_neer were Common & Unpopular once. It was their dedication, consistency and work that they have reached this milestone (step hy step)
Such Fake influencer Scams are very common these days. Scammers will make such accounts, bait you & get lakhs of followers within days & then would sell the page (The page name would be Changed by the buyer to run their business).
& i feel weird to see that the many hardworking influencers are working day & night but their growth is so slow (not talking about my ownself). People would watch them, keep a check on them but would never show any support. 
But the same people would Follow & support such fake pages like @zarainfluencer.in (& many more) kz of their own benefits & their temptations for freebies.
.
Anyways, Hope you liked the video. Share it with all those Bholi janta😅
.

latestPosts.caption:
From 1 subscriber to 1 crore subscribers — this journey has been so, so beautiful ✨ 10Million 😭 Not just because of the numbers… But because of the love , the struggles , the lessons , and the people we met along the way❤️
We received our Diamond Play Button 💎 two months ago… And we didn’t unbox it right away — not because we forgot, But because we wanted to make it special ✨ We wanted to open it with the special people 🥰who made this possible.
We worked day and night 🌞🌙, especially in 2024 — Uploading with consistency , fighting self-doubt , pushing through burnout 😌— Believing that one day, the world would see what we see 🌍
And today, we hold this button in our hands 🙌 But honestly? It feels like we’re holding a piece of every single heart ❤️ that clicked “subscribe 🔔.”
Thank you — for believing in a dream that started with just one view 👀 This moment is yours just as much as it’s ours 💖

A Heartfelt Thanks To My Family 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 for the endless love , support , and patience — @iamhardikpahwa @dailyanubhav 
Thanks to My Team that stood behind every idea 💡, every video — @jiteshjhandaii @khushi_shrma._ @mahak.rukhaya & for making perfect party arrangements 🎉 

Special Thanks to My Friends 🫶 for their constant support — @shagunbagla @paras.mehtaaa @sanjana_jagga30 telling me you are proud of me)& @laghvi_taneja (specially for providing us a permanent school location)😍

@tech_iela You couldn’t be there at the party, but your presence has always been felt in every step of this journey. As my guide, teacher, and counsellor, Thankyou for always being there.

Special Thanks To My YouTube Managers👨‍💻 — @tejo_lenka (for supporting me throughout my journey) @eshaoberoi (for helping me bring this play button home)

Special Thanks to My Agency @iplixmedia @sanskarbajajj @radhikaa.sharmaaa for believing in my vision 🌟

Special Thanks to — @youtube @youtubeindia @youtubecreatorsindia ❤️ for the endless love

Thanks to @yash_photography_fatehabad for capturing beautiful moments 📸

The kind of experience that makes you smile like you’re 7 again 🐘🌞 I used to be obsessed with elephants—back when elephant babas would come down the street near my house, and I’d beg for a ride every time. It’s been years since I saw one up close. I was actually planning a trip to Kerala just to relive my childhood love for elephants — but by pure chance, I found out about elephant rides near Amer village in Jaipur , Monica (yes, that’s her name!) brought all those childhood memories rushing back.. it was pure magic then, and somehow, it still is.
